<body><div class=WordSection1>
<div class="brand">📚 ENGLISH CODING · 영어코딩</div>
<h1>⚔️ RB004 Week 8 — English Worksheet (Beginner)</h1>
<p><strong>Topic:</strong> Ship It — Publish &amp; Playtest Party · <strong>Course:</strong> Arena Legends · <strong>Level:</strong> Beginner · <strong>Time:</strong> about 30 minutes</p>
<p>This is launch week. You <strong>publish</strong> your arena, make it <strong>Public</strong>, and join the class <strong>playtest party</strong> — everyone plays everyone's arena.</p>
<hr />
<h2>1 · Predict 🔮</h2>
<p>These are pieces of a round loop like yours. Find the matching part in <strong>YOUR</strong> script, then circle or write your answer.</p>
<pre><code class="language-lua">status.Value = &quot;Intermission...&quot;
task.wait(10)
</code></pre>
<p><strong>Does YOUR game have an intermission before the round? Circle one:</strong> yes · no</p>
<p><strong>How many seconds is it?</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<pre><code class="language-lua">if points.Red &gt;= Settings.WinScore then
    status.Value = &quot;Red team wins!&quot;
end
</code></pre>
<p><strong>Open YOUR Settings ModuleScript. Is your <code>WinScore</code> bigger than 1? Circle one:</strong> yes · no</p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<hr />
<h2>2 · Find the Difference 🐛</h2>
<p>These are <strong>launch checklist</strong> settings, not scripts. Each pair shows the good setting first, then a broken one. Circle what's different and write one short sentence about the problem.</p>
<p><strong>Pair A</strong> — Your whole class should be able to join at the same time.</p>
<pre><code>-- good
Maximum Player Count: 10
</code></pre>
<pre><code>-- broken
Maximum Player Count: 1
</code></pre>
<p><strong>What is wrong? What happens at the playtest party?</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<p><strong>Pair B</strong> — Your classmates need to be able to join your game.</p>
<pre><code>-- good
Playability: Public
</code></pre>
<pre><code>-- broken
Playability: Private
</code></pre>
<p><strong>What is wrong?</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<hr />
<h2>3 · Fill the Gap ✏️</h2>
<p>This SpawnLocation should be for the <strong>Red team only</strong>, so <code>Neutral</code> must be off. One word is missing. Fill it in using the word bank.</p>
<pre><code>SpawnLocation → Properties
Neutral: ____
TeamColor: Bright red
</code></pre>
<p><strong>Word bank:</strong> <code>false</code> · <code>true</code> · <code>red</code></p>
<p><strong>Write the missing word:</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<hr />
<h2>4 · Tell Me What You Built 📸</h2>
<p>Now publish your arena: <strong>File → Publish to Roblox</strong>, then Game Settings → Permissions → <strong>Public</strong>. Join the class playtest party. When you finish, come back here.</p>
<p>Send a photo or video of your published game page or classmates in your arena, then explain. Use these sentence starters — write 2 or 3 sentences.</p>
<blockquote>
<p>My game mode is …</p>
<p>My favorite script in my game is …</p>
<p>When my classmates played my arena, …</p>
</blockquote>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<hr />
<h2>5 · Record Your Walkthrough 🎥</h2>
<p>Take a video on your phone (or a parent's phone) — this one is your <strong>launch trailer</strong>. Talk like you are showing your game to a new player. Try to use these words: <strong>publish</strong>, <strong>Public</strong>, <strong>round</strong>.</p>
<blockquote>
<ol>
<li>Show your game page on Roblox and say its name.</li>
<li>Play part of a round: spawn, score, winner message.</li>
<li>Show your favorite script and say what it does.</li>
</ol>
</blockquote>
<p><strong>Write what you will say in your video.</strong> You can read from it while filming.</p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<hr />
<h3>Submit ✅</h3>
<p>Send this worksheet + your walkthrough video to teacher on KakaoTalk.</p>
<div class="footer">영어코딩 · <b>english-coding.co.uk</b></div>
</div></body></html>
